* Support managing calendars, travel, preparing for presentations, company meetings and other key events;
* Assemble and coordinate key project status information related to development and release;
* Plan travel itineraries and make travel arrangements, including reservations for events and dining as needed;
* Prepare, compile and manage expense reports for travel following established company and travel policy guidelines;
* Assist with general department tasks, including conference room requests, ordering supplies, coordinating general maintenance and upgrades for office equipment, phones, computers, etc.;
* Coordinate both on-site and off-site workshops, events and demos, including internal and external partners, vendors, and collaborators;
* Partner and work extensively with internal departments and external vendors to provide and/or receive necessary information, materials, approvals, updates, etc.; and
* Greet guests and assist with special projects relating to guests/visitors.

* General administrative experience supporting executives in a corporate environment;
* Strong written and verbal communication;
* Ability to successfully interact with a wide range of Imagineers, senior executives, vendors;
* Willingness to experiment with new forms of asynchronous communication as our hybrid workstyle continues to evolve;
* High interest in technology and software product development; and
* A culture add.

* Experience at The Walt Disney Company;
* Experience working with Imagineering a plus;
* Experience working in a large public corporation; and
* Experience with video Teleconferencing (VTC) equipment, Slack, Zoom.

Responsibilities include, but not limited to:

* Think ahead about little things that can turn into big problems and be proactive in finding a solution; 
* Prioritize workload according to Project deadlines and handle interruptions through-out the day with an approachable attitude and assist Project Team when an emergency arises;
* Use teamwork to do the job better, faster, smarter;
* Plan events like birthdays, service anniversary recognition parties, lunch-and-learns and team-building activities;
* Assist with on-boarding new employees – you’ll be the “friendly face” that newbies count on to answer all their questions;
* Schedule meetings, along with reserving a conference room, for the Project Team. In most cases (given the bi-coastal nature of the project), set-up meeting with Zoom video calls;
* Develop working knowledge of conference room systems and assist Project Team when needed;
* Order food for breakfast/lunch meetings and assist with set-up/clean-up;
* Assist in planning Team events, including in-office functions, virtual gatherings (via Zoom), and remote events (at/near Disneyland Resort, at/near Glendale offices, etc);
* Via Concur and American Express, book travel for Project Team as well as RSR requests for contractors and vendors as needed. Prior to booking any travel, ensure Travel Authorization has been signed and approved by the Project Team Leadership and Finance. Also secure required job number for expensing;
* Via Concur, complete expense reports on behalf of Team members;
* Enter backstage gate clearances into EZ Lobby as requested by Project Team;
* If requested, take meeting notes for any Project Team meeting;
* Work with Direct Leader to incorporate additions, changes, or deletions within the Project Team into seating arrangements and tap access into the building;
* Obtain Green Badges for Project Contractors, Independent Contractors, and Vendors;
* Generate Purchase Orders and check requests, as needed, in SAP;
* Make an inventory of the office supplies, then devise a more efficient way to keep things in stock for your specific Project Team;
* Adhere to Project Intellectual Protection Guidelines by watermarking confidential documents, posting onto Project Team BOX sites, as needed, and securing/shredding documents left at printers, plotters, or conference rooms;
* Enter your time into required system (SAP or IQN) on a weekly basis by following the company’s guideline for Accurate Time Recording; and
* Complete all required Computer Based Training in D-Learn in a timely manner.

* Minimum two years in a Secretary role;
* Strong organizational and follow-through skills, orderly and detail-oriented with ability to handle multiple work streams simultaneously, prioritize work and accurately and efficiently archive documents and work products Ability to appropriately respond to and resolve issues with little direction;
* Excellent written, verbal and interpersonal communication skills to assure professional interaction with senior executives, internal partners, and external contacts;
* Strong command of English grammar skills with an ability to prepare correspondence from notes, meetings and author documents and reports;
* Ability to work effectively in a team environment;
* Ability to manage time wisely and prioritize effectively;
* Ability to anticipate needs, take initiative, proactively solve problems and use sound judgment;
* Demonstrated ability to handle confidential and sensitive information;
* Enthusiastic attitude and strong work ethic; and
* Strong computer/technology skills, including but not limited to Microsoft Outlook, Concur, SAP (T&E, Life Events, Time Processor, Employee ESS, Casual Buyer), Internet Explorer and internet-based research, and video teleconferencing systems and services.

Responsibilities include, but not limited to:

* Proactively review your leader’s schedule daily and weekly in Microsoft Outlook so you understand the team’s priorities and also keep things in mind like travel and work time;
* Keep an inventory of the office supplies, then devise a more efficient way to keep things in stock for your specific Project Team; 
* Generate Purchase Orders and check requests, as needed, in SAP; 
* Schedule meetings, along with reserving a conference room and Zoom dial-in as needed, for Project Team;
* Handle interruptions through-out the day with an approachable attitude and assist Project Team when an emergency arises;
* Periodically take meeting notes for any Project Team meeting;
* Adhere to Project Intellectual Protection Guidelines by watermarking confidential documents, posting onto Project Team BOX sites, as needed, and securing/shredding documents left at printers, plotters, or conference rooms; 
* Order food for breakfast/lunch meetings. Assist with set-up and clean-up; 
* Via Concur and American Express, book travel for Project Team including RSR requests for contractors and vendors as needed following all appropriate approval processes;
* Enter backstage gate clearances into EZ Lobby as requested by Project Team;
* Work with IT on behalf of Direct Leader for any SAP or computer issues;
* Provide back-up support for Front Reception Desk when needed;
* Assist with scheduling interviews for Direct Leader;
* Assist with on-boarding new employees – you’ll be the “friendly face” that newbies count on to answer all their questions; 
* Advise Executive Assistant of any additions, changes, or deletions within the Project Team in seating arrangements and tap access into the building. Also, work with Executive Assistant on obtaining Green Badges for Project Contractors, Independent Contractors, and Vendors;
* If requested, assist your Direct Leader and Project Team with entering their time into SAP or IQN;
* Think ahead about little things that can turn into big problems and be proactive in finding a solution as well as prioritize workload according to Project deadlines; and
* Plan events like birthdays, service anniversary recognition parties, lunch-and-learns and team-building activities.

* Minimum two years in a Secretary role;
* Excellent written, verbal and interpersonal communication skills to assure professional interaction with senior executives, internal partners, and external contacts;
* Strong command of English grammar skills with an ability to prepare correspondence from notes, meetings and author documents and reports;
* Strong organizational and follow-through skills, orderly and detail-oriented with ability to handle multiple work streams simultaneously, prioritize work and accurately and efficiently archive documents and work products Ability to appropriately respond to and resolve issues with little direction;
* Ability to work effectively in a team environment;
* Ability to manage time wisely and prioritize effectively;
* Ability to anticipate needs, take initiative, proactively solve problems and use sound judgment;
* Demonstrated ability to handle confidential and sensitive information;
* Enthusiastic attitude and strong work ethic;
* Working knowledge of conference room systems; and
* Strong computer/technology skills, including but not limited to Microsoft Word, Excel, Outlook, PowerPoint, Visio, SharePoint, Concur, SAP (T&E, Life Events, Time Processor, Employee ESS, Casual Buyer), Internet Explorer and internet-based research, and video teleconferencing systems and services.

These teams are responsible for the integration of TWDC Franchises (i.e. Marvel & Lucas) into Park experiences along with the integration of third party partners into our parks globally. Additionally, this team leads the story development needs of all park experiences globally as well as framing up and developing IP for TWDC content teams. This is a unique opportunity for anyone looking to further develop their skills in a fun, fast moving dynamic environment. This joint team is closely aligned with many studio, tv, Disney+ partners so experience in that world is ideal. It goes without saying that there will be expense reports, travel planning, and heavy calendar jockeying, but this job is very much about people. The relationship you form with the executives you support is absolutely critical, because that’s what enables you to become a true partner. In addition to understanding your executives business -- and business needs -- inside and out, you’ll also need to develop deep knowledge of the leadership and workings of WDI and of related departments across the Disney enterprise. As the “face” of your executives within The Walt Disney Company, your professionalism, loyalty and attitude are a reflection of the office, and as such, are a key component to its success. Every day as an Executive Support Professional is different! On any given day you might:

* Manage a very busy calendar on behalf of your executive. You’ll work with colleagues across TWDC and Imagineering, as well as with many different Disney executives across Studios, Disney+, Consumer Products and external production companies;
* Assist with other Franchise, Partnership and Story Team members with various administrative, departmental and office needs;
* Conduct research, fact-check existing work, and prepare agendas and summaries pending the meeting needs. You’ll have tasks that you “own” completely and will provide regular assistance on others;
* Create global, multi-city travel itineraries, taking into account time zones, weather delays, traffic and fatigue levels;
* Interface directly with other senior executives and their support teams – your ability to work well with people on all levels is a very important part of your job;
* Review your leader’s schedule to build-in time for things like thinking and traveling to their next meeting or be mindful of the different timezones partners are working in;
* Understand the day’s priorities so you can be strategic about how you direct phone calls and set meetings;
* Schedule conference rooms, meetings and zoom chats;
* Be ready to throw the entire schedule out the door when an emergency comes up, then pick it up again when the dust settles;
* Handle extremely confidential, sensitive information, remembering that Disney is a publicly traded company;
* Draft letters and emails on behalf of your leaders;
* Assist with on-boarding new employees – you’ll be the “friendly face” that newbies count on to answer all their questions, including some who are extremely senior in the organization;
* Manage large purchase orders and vendor contracts or any office supply needs;
* Mentor and train other support professionals in hard skills like computer programs, and soft skills like teamwork; and
* Plan your executive involvement in large, high-profile events like premiers, product launches, off-sites and team-building activities.

Here’s what you will need to be successful in this role:

* Sharp written and verbal communication skills, including flawless grammar and a rich vocabulary;
* Desire to immerse yourself fully and learn all aspects of your executive’s business;
* Ability to multi-task and prioritize deadlines/deliverables;
* Strong proficiency with all types of computers, phones and office equipment, as well as mastery of Microsoft Office programs, SAP, Confluence, Concur, and working in a Windows environment;
* A calm head and steady hand to deal with the unexpected;
* “EQ” skills to build bridges, forge alliances and encourage people to want to work with you;
* Complete reliability handling confidential, often highly sensitive information;
* Desire to truly be helpful to your leaders and co-workers, to go the extra mile without being asked. Resourcefulness is key;
* Some flexibility in your schedule – we value work/life balance, but in a pinch, a bit more time is needed;
* Very strong organizational skills and extreme attention to detail; 
* A highly professional demeanor, positive outlook and a can-do attitude; and
* Strong professionalism and discretion.

It would be great if you also had these skills:

* At least 5 years supporting an executive and/or equivalent experience;
* Experience at The Walt Disney Company;
* Experience working in a large public corporation; 
* Experience working with Creative teams and executives;
* Familiarity and experience working with TV & film related teams; and
* Excellent knowledge of MAC computers and software such as Keynote.
